The Hollow Kingdom Trilogy is a fantasy trilogy written by Clare B. Dunkle with many roots in British folklore and Scandinavian myths. The series includes The Hollow Kingdom, Close Kin, In the Coils of the Snake and a number of short stories published on Dunkle's official website. The Hollow Kingdom won the 2004 Mythopoeic Fantasy Award for Children's Literature.Important themes in the series include racism, prejudice, and cultural diversity.